The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 21 January is 32,586 (3,771.6 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 16 January, there were 4,346 new confirmed cases (503.0 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 09 January, there were 5,549 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 22% (1,203 fewer cases).
